		</script><div class="wide-photo-box"  ><img src="http://thinkprogress.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/apimages_guinea-worm-638x417.jpg" alt="7-year-old Ajak Kuol Nyamchiek  watches while John Lotiki, a nurse with the Carter Center, bandages the blister on her leg from where a guinea worm is slowly emerging in Abuyong, Sudan in 2010" />
